	<article id="post-3496" class="post-3496 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-accountability category-big-brother category-civil-liberties category-current-affairs category-democracy category-drones-2 category-gchq category-intelligence category-isc category-law category-mi5 category-mi6 category-national-security category-politics category-privacy-2 category-snowden category-spies category-surveillance category-tv category-whistleblowers tag-accountability-2 tag-bbc tag-bbc-world tag-gchq tag-intelligence-2 tag-isc tag-mi5 tag-mi6 tag-oversight tag-public-hearing tag-spies-2 tag-uk">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/11/bbc-world-interview-re-uk-spy-accountability.html" title="Permalink to BBC World interview re UK spy accountability" rel="bookmark"><span class="caps">BBC</span> World interview re <span class="caps">UK</span> spy accountability</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/11/bbc-world-interview-re-uk-spy-accountability.html" title="23:42" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2013-11-28T23:42:02+00:00" pubdate>November 28, 2013</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="byauthor">Annie Machon</span></span></span><br>
                                <a href="#" onclick="javascript:copyToClipboard('http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/11/bbc-world-interview-re-uk-spy-accountability.html')">Copy permalink to clipboard</a>
                                <br>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>Here’s a recent inter­view I did for <span class="caps">BBC</span> World about the three top Brit­ish spies deign­ing, for the first time ever, to be pub­licly ques­tioned by the Intel­li­gence and Secur­ity Com­mit­tee in par­lia­ment, which has a notional over­sight role:<br />
<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/80539105" height="281" width="500" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>
<p><a href="http://vimeo.com/80539105"><span class="caps">BBC</span> World inter­view on <span class="caps">UK</span> Par­laiment­ary hear­ings on <span class="caps">NSA</span>/Snowden affair</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/anniemachon">Annie Machon</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>
<p>It sub­sequently emerged that they only agreed to appear if they were <a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2508779/Spy-chiefs-fed-questions-advance-parliamentary-committee-hearing.html">told the ques­tions in advance</a>.  So much for this <a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2013/10/empire-strikes-back.html">already incred­ibly lim­ited over­sight</a> cap­ab­il­ity in a notional West­ern democracy.….</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
